$values.Comment: CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the IDs of the Binary run for this Filament
CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the IDs of the Request (PoV or Poll) executing this Filament
CSV (up to 4 values) of strings indicating whether a Request is a PoV or a Poll
CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the IDs of Teams; used for coloration only.  8 colors the Filament 'reference' gray, and -1 colors the Filament based on the team that fielded the PoV

CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the IDs of the Execution to render; providing this fetches a trace directly by Execution ID, which bypasses fetching the ID by Binary and Request ID, however this will cause default values to show in the disassembly window
CSV (up to 4 values) of integers indicating how many instructions to skip rendering in the Filament.  Does not create empty space.

CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the counts of instructions to render in a given Filament.  If a value is provided in InstructionSkips, this value indicates how many instructions after the first rendered to visualize.
CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the number of instructions to offset each render.  The effect is visual only, and is used to align interesting sections of two or more different Filaments.
CSV (up to 4 values) of integers with the IDs of the IDS to use
CSV (up to 4 values) of booleans detailing whether or not to pulse Filaments for visibliity
A boolean indicating whether or not to display the disassembly readout
A boolean indicating whether or not to display the communications readout
A boolean indicating whether or not to display annotations on the Filament
A boolean indicating whether or not to display the Memory View alongside each Filament
A boolean indicating whether or not to overlay the Filaments, such that they occupy the same space; useful for quickly showing differences in Filaments
A boolean indicating whether or not to display the disassembly window across the entire screen; this will prevent the Filaments from rendering, as they would be obscured anyway
Global parm for toggling features of this package
Copy bounds and trace index to prep for enumeration
Position plane and dot cursor using data store
Set up indices and their float forms
A float indicating how large in the Z direction each individual instruction in the Filament should step

$values.Note: A boolean indicating whether or not the cursor can be manipulated by a human operator while recording
A serialized set of steps that, if set, overrides the default choreography and instead uses a basic sequence to dictate camera movement
